 Data Definition Language (DDL)
 DDL commands are used to define the database structure.

CREATE: Used to create a new table, database, index, or view.

sql
Copy code
CREATE TABLE Employees (
    EmployeeID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    FirstName VARCHAR(50),
    LastName VARCHAR(50),
    HireDate DATE
);


ALTER: Used to modify an existing table structure (add, modify, or drop columns).
ALTER TABLE Employees ADD Salary DECIMAL(10, 2);

DROP: Used to delete a table, database, index, or view.
DROP TABLE Employees;

TRUNCATE: Used to remove all records from a table without removing the table structure.
TRUNCATE TABLE Employees;